    {
        "content": "<p>I just stumbled upon this. Shouldn't <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.subperm_append_left#doc\">docs#List.subperm_append_left</a> in batteries rather be called <code>List.append_subperm_append_left</code>, analogous to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.append_sublist_append_left#doc\">docs#List.append_sublist_append_left</a> in Init? And then the following could be added, the analogue of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.sublist_append_left#doc\">docs#List.sublist_append_left</a> <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span> </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Batteries</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Perm</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">subperm_append_left'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">l₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l₂</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l₁</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Subperm</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">l₁</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">++</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l₂</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">l₁</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">case</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cons</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">head</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tail</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IH</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subperm_cons</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">head</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IH</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(And the same for <code>..._right</code>.)</p>",
        "id": 537649047,
        "sender_full_name": "Malvin Gattinger",
        "timestamp": 1756985103
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, that seems sensible. I'd try to get the rename in before the next version bump middle of the month, and then add the new ones after</p>",
        "id": 537657786,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1756988059
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool, thank you!</p>",
        "id": 537661185,
        "sender_full_name": "Malvin Gattinger",
        "timestamp": 1756989116
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A maybe related question: I noticed that <code>aesop</code> often does not find simple proofs like <code>exact List.Subperm.trans h1 h2</code>, even though <code>exact?</code> found these in most cases. Are there some annotations missing to let <code>aesop</code> use lemmas like this?</p>\n<p>And similarly, why is <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Subperm.refl#doc\">docs#List.Subperm.refl</a> marked with <code>@[refl]</code> but not with <code>@[simp]</code>, in contrast to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=List.Sublist.refl#doc\">docs#List.Sublist.refl</a> <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 537661194,
        "sender_full_name": "Malvin Gattinger",
        "timestamp": 1756989117
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or have this new one be called <code>List.subperm_left_append</code> (and maybe also <code>List.sublist_left_append</code>)?<br>\nEdit: or <code>List.left_subperm_append</code> / <code>List.left_sublist_append</code>?</p>",
        "id": 537670901,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1756991989
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In lean 3, <code>simp</code> would try theorems tagged with <code>@[refl]</code> in more places, if I understand correctly. Adding <code>@[simp]</code> as well is sort of a workaround for that change, but one that I'd support</p>",
        "id": 537703574,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1757000842
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(To clarify, I'm not a decision maker for anything related to Batteries)</p>",
